details.description: In the eclectic South End neighborhood, Babaloo Coffee Club invites you to indulge in a world of exquisite flavors. Step inside and be greeted by the rich aroma of freshly brewed coffee, enticing sandwiches, handcrafted empanadas, and delectable seasonal sweets. Unwind in a warm and inviting ambiance, perfect for catching up with friends. Babaloo Coffee Club is your go-to destination for a delightful sensory journey that celebrates the art of coffee

reviews_data.review_text: I really recommend you to try the Matcha with strawberries The best out of the best 😍😍😍 most of our let’s talk about Jimena service amazing and beautiful personality

It's expensive for what it's regular drinks, the drinks didn't have the extraordinary flavor that they supposedly had with the name and ingredients, they don't have the option of a children's cup with a lid, the drinks had too much ice and little flavor.

reviews_data.review_text: I absolutely love this place! Best coffee in Charlotte 🩷
I love this place! Best coffe in Charlotte
El servicio es excelente Jimena Quiros la mejor
Spectacular atmosphere. It has become my favorite place to share and meet new people. The best coffee and Jimena is the best coffee barista!
I love the matcha coconut it’s my favorite, all the staffing is amazing Jimena is so sweet
Jimena was such a great person it was my first time here and she was so patient with me and giving me reviews on other drinks to try as well for sure, I’ll be back
Literally best matcha in town!!! great staff and environment

I usually go for breakfast on my days off, the service is great, Franco is super nice and I love how he makes the matcha and coffe! Definitely recommend going to grab something, everything is so good, no disappointments yet!
I loved the place. I love the decor and every single service. The barista Franco was very nice; he was the friendliest person and provided excellent service.
The work environment was super cool. I love the coffee and the banana pudding was 10/10. Another dish that I loved was the matcha timarisu.
Cute coffee shop! I took my dog with me and the barista gave him a heart shaped cookie and they have water bowls for dogs too!
The barista is the sweetest! But oh my gosh best tiramisu latte I’ve ever come across! Nailed the flavors completely. Everything was so aesthetically pleasing as well. 10/10
Anytime Jimena works I get some of the best matcha in the city!! I cannot recommend this hidden gem enough! I haven't had a drink there I haven't loved
Iced latte with vanilla and almond milk + tip was $9. Unfortunately, it did not taste like a $9 latte. Might depend on what you get.

review_questions.Seating type: Indoor dining area, Outdoor patio / terrace

reviews_data.review_text:
I tried the banana matcha, and it was pretty good—I'd give it around a 3.8 out of 5. I didn't try any food, but it looked tempting.

When I first walked up, I honestly felt like I was stepping into Spain—the atmosphere is stunning and very aesthetic. The indoor seating is cozy and a bit tight, so it’s not really a place to work comfortably, but there’s plenty of outdoor space to relax and enjoy.

The service was excellent—friendly and attentive.

Price-wise, I think it's a bit steep for a matcha, but all in all, it’s a cool spot. I plan to come back soon to try the food next time.

more of an aesthetic instagram coffee place than a good one. Tasted mediocre and the tiramisu latte just tasted like strong coffee. Expensive, wait is long, no where to sit and they messed up my order (they did fix it though). my bf loved the empanadas so I would come back for that, but driving out of the way for this coffee isn’t worth it.
They have the best matcha in CLT! We tried the blueberry banana matcha which was our favorite, and the popular strawberry matcha. The lady who made our matcha was super nice

Jimena was amazing! We went for coffee today and she had a line out the door and despite being all by herself she provided great customer service and always had a smile on her face. Coffee was delicious as always.
Place is DOPE🔥

After he ate too fast and got bad hiccups, he went to get some coffee to settle his stomach. While this place was really evolved and fun and had weird flavors, something that Mi Hijo likes, he got a double shot in his coffee!

And that’s when the trouble started, worse than when he’s had too much sugar. You better believe we took stock of the situation when he got home!

Very cool place, though!

review_questions.Noise level: Loud, but you can still talk

reviews_data.review_text: What a cool little spot to say the least! Good outdoor seating options, very cute and quaint cafe inside with a lot of menu options and a very creative drink menu. I felt like I asked a million questions to Alesandro and he patiently and diligently walked me through the whole menu (which he was extremely knowledgeable about) and ended up landing on the Biscoff Latte which had about 3 different layer and a very complex flavor profile and structure, but was very good! Would love to be me back as a treat!!
Love the industrial design. The coffee shop is not large, but cozy
Best matcha combination I’ve had. Love the pandan juice with matcha a lot.
My favorite coffee shop in the city!

I hate to be that person but..

I go to new coffee shop every two days to study and finish up some work. I always get the regular black coffee everywhere to try it.

The service and the young lady that was at the register were amazing, she was fast and very nice.

The coffee:- I did not even get to my third sip, I had to stop, the coffee tasted burnt and very over roasty taste.
I dont think I will be going back there for coffee but they have a nice patio outside and easy parking access on the street for a quick coffee.

They have interesting coffee and other drinks here. I love their strawberry matcha! The pastry case has just a few options, but they are all good. They have expanded their seating since they first opened and streamlined their service, so it’s faster.

i went here with my two friends and had a strawberry matcha which was the best strawberry matcha i’ve ever had, not very syurpy because they had actual purée! The matcha was smooth and very nice. My friend had the banana blueberry matcha and it was so creative and delicious i will probably get that next time, it was also a beautiful day so sitting in the spot with the big door open was really nice!  ( ^_^ )

Cute little coffee shop with outdoor sitting in addition to the quaint seating inside. The barista was friendly and my honey cinnamon oat milk latte is delicious.  My daughter enjoyed a Blue Cloud Banana Matcha.

The best coffee I have ever had! I stumbled upon this place and ordered the tiramisu latte and it was like a dessert - it was soooo good! The guy working there took his time making the drinks but you definitely get great quality coffee. Loved it!
Freddo cap & biscoff latte
Blue cloud banana matcha is the best matcha I have ever had! 10/10 quality and service! Will return!
Great 😊

I really wanted to love this place after seeing their matcha online—it looked amazing. The service was great and the barista was super friendly, which I appreciated. However, the matcha itself just didn’t live up to the hype. At $9, I was expecting something much better in terms of flavor and quality. The space is small, which I don’t mind at all, but unfortunately, the drink just didn’t deliver.

I went to this place for the first time on my break for an ice latte. Barista recommend a Freddy Cappuccino, that was out of this world, absolutely recommended. Service was great, if I have to choose a reason to come back will be the service.
Grwat coffee ane nice staff. The cuban sandwich is delicious
Small, cute & quaint shop with incredible service. One of the best Matchas in Charlotte hands down.
Waited inside 20 minutes for an online order. Staff didn’t even acknowledge me the entire time. Good coffee, but wont be back

Called in to order empanadas + pan de bono - to my surprise it was packed on a Sunday morning - yet my order was ready within minutes. Such a nice vibe and great customer service. Empanadas were delicious - pan de bono was a little thinner than other places I frequent but good taste - I’m glad to see the family grow in different businesses - good job Emanuel !!

review_questions.Parking options: Paid parking lot, Free street parking

reviews_data.review_text: Loved the strawberry matcha and their Cuban sandwich. Their pistachio milk is delicious. Been coming here since day one and babaloo just keep getting better. Their baristas are always so nice
Great coffee and staff! I love their strawberry matcha with pistachio milk. Their alt milks are delicious and they make it in house. Empanadas are also delicious

This coffee shop is absolutely beautiful, but the drinks were a huge letdown. With all the hype on Instagram, I had high expectations. I ordered the pistachio latte, hoping for a rich, flavorful drink, but it tasted like straight-up pistachio milk—no espresso at all. The service was great, but there’s no way this was worth $8. I don’t get how people actually enjoy these drinks.

cute place but the MILK is sooo gross. the drink itself was not good. i got a strawberry matcha and it was just so not good. any milk alternative is not good taste awful i had almond and oat and it was sooo nasty. wouldn’t recommend tbh cute place good service just the drinks itself not good.  could have such amazing potential if a few things were changed
Wonderful small shop with great people. Freddo cappuccino is a must try!

Ordered a strawberry matcha, it was not very enjoyable. Whatever oatmilk brand they use is not it. The strawberry did not come through well either. I came hoping to work from this spot but it is really only good for grab and go. Staff was nice though. I plan on never returning unfortunately.
Unimpressed watered down coffee late

Unfortunately I had high expectations for this place after seeing so many great reviews and IG posts I was eager to try. I love Colombian food so personally I wanted to try them out.

I ordered the strawberry matcha with oat milk and empanadas, unfortunately was disappointed. The matcha flavor was not present my drink tasted like low calorie strawberry nesquik. I’ve tried many other matcha’s from other coffee shops so definitely I was able to taste the difference.

The empanadas weren’t that bad but I’ve tried other places that have better options at a better price. The place is super small so it’s more like a quick to go option, hopefully they improve their matcha and buy better quality ingredients. But honestly, I wouldn’t recommend this place.

I recently visited Babaloo and was drawn in by the beautiful aesthetic; despite the location being very small with minimal space to wait in line/ wait for drinks.

As a matcha girly, I was really looking forward to trying their matcha, and unfortunately, it fell short of expectations. The flavor was overwhelmingly dominated by oat milk and strawberries, with barely any discernible matcha taste. It was a disappointment, especially given the high standards set by the shop's presence on social media, atmosphere and service.

I would not recommend. However, I do believe Babaloo has a lot of potential. The service was top-notch, with friendly and attentive staff who made me feel welcome.

Best thing about visiting this coffee place: seeing them give a fur baby a pup cup.

Probably the best Matcha I’ve had in the Charlotte area. Sweetest barista, and one of the only matchas I’ve had that I’ve loved without any cold foam. Top notch, and completely worth the slightly higher price point.
The best coffee I've tried in Charlotte, and such a great atmosphere! The craft drinks are made so perfectly, they're not overly sweet☕ Thanks so much, Babaloo coffee club, for the amazing service!
came here with a friend and we have both been around the world. it is really difficult to find quality coffee and matcha in the states, especially in charlotte. babaloo absolutely blew us away!
so fab,, so chic,, so cute!! to say its a vibe is an understatement. babaloos subtle wordly, koi taste is v refreshing 🍵🤍

Great Coffee, Amazing Food & Atmosphere

The coffee is solid, nothing extraordinary, but definitely good for the price. Where this place really shines is in its food and atmosphere. The design of the coffee shop is great, creating a welcoming and enjoyable vibe. I tried the chorizo and beef empanadas, and both were delicious, each served with its own sauce that complemented the flavors well. My only complaint is that the music was way too loud, but overall, it’s a fun spot worth visiting!

The aesthetic was very cute & trendy, but the cafe only has two really small tables for dine-in which is unfortunate if you want to sit & enjoy your items but I suppose works if you want to get your coffee to-go. The staff were very friendly! Overall, the food was reasonably priced, two items for $10. The mini empanada was good, the plain cappuccino was okay not great.

It's a cool little shop with good vibes and aesthetics, but the drinks were very disappointing for how expensive they are. The strawberry matcha barely had any strawberry or flavor, and the red velvet oatmilk latte tasted like oatmilk and nothing else. For the price your paying for the drinks, it's just not worth it for the lack of flavor. Good customer service and staff though.

Babaloo is a hidden gem for coffee lovers! The atmosphere is warm and inviting, perfect for catching up with friends.. I highly recommend their specialty drinks, especially the strawberry matcha 🍵🤍 The staff is friendly and attentive, making the experience even better. Plus, their pastries and snacks are delicious, with great options for different tastes like empanadas, or sandwiches. Plus some sweet like the cuatro leches cake or the alfajores (my favoriteeeeee). Babaloo is definitely worth a visit!

This coffee shop is really good! From the moment you walk in, the rich aroma of freshly brewed coffee fills the air. The flavors are bold, smooth, and perfectly balanced—just how real coffee should be!

The atmosphere is warm and inviting, with a cozy charm. It has a small indoor space; however, it’s a great place to connect with the community. I made great connections in less than an hour.
The staff is incredibly friendly and passionate about their craft, and they are also bilingual.

Babaloo is a must-visit. I highly recommend their matcha and their empanadas—absolutely tasty! Can't wait to come back.

Coffee was delicious, very unique way to serve it, what I love the most it’s that they don’t add too much of syrups so actually tastes like coffee, only thing that I didn’t like is the size of they sitting area hahahah I wish they added more space because the concept and the products are very nice.

Overall, it is a really cute little shop! It was so tiny inside that there wasn’t really anywhere to stand while you waited on your drink, which made it kind of awkward. One strawberry matcha was over $9, which feels a bit overpriced for the quality of the drink.
Best coffee shop in Charlotte! ⭐️. The turkey club sandwich was amazing!!. And is also pet friendly :)
Super excelente todo la atención de Daniela me hace volver por su buen servicio el café y el lugar super para una plática con las amigas

I absolutely loved Babaloo Coffee Club the first couple of times I went—it was so good that I even went back-to-back! I made two TikToks about it and referred a few friends because I was genuinely impressed.

However, my recent visits have been disappointing. I’ve been back three more times, and each time the strawberry matcha had less and less strawberry purée. Today, I even specifically asked them to please put the normal amount since the last time it was lacking, but I still only got one tiny layer. The strawberry matcha costs more than the regular matcha, so I expect a decent amount of strawberry, especially since their prices are higher than other matcha places I frequent.

I’m worried that they gave us their "best of the best" during their opening but are now slowly declining in quality. I do enjoy the empanadas, but at $4 each, they’re quite small and not filled enough to feel worth it.

I really hope they address these issues because I want to love this place as much as I did at first.
Love this place ! Everything is delicious, great and fast Service

reviews_data.review_text: Best matcha and pan de Bono’s 💌📩
The best Coffee Shop in Charlotte, the service is 10/10.
El café está genial y las empanadas súper. Fui con mi esposa y me encantó el fredo capuccino con dulce de leche

Sorry to leave a bad review. This place is tiny with two tables. Doesn’t have much of an ambience. The prices don’t make any sense. I buy a tall coffee at Starbucks for $2.87 and I thought that is expensive. These guys charge five dollars for a tall drip coffee. They also charge $.30 for cream. The breakfast sandwich was eight dollars and not that great. I spent 15 bucks for a coffee and a sandwich. The owner needs a reality check. Fix the quality of food and your prices and you may have a chance of surviving. My guess is they’re not gonna be open for too long.
Primera  y ultima vez que voy...mala atencion, todos apresurados y para el colmo mi cafe con un pelo

I ordered the strawberry matcha with an empanada. Best combo.
My husband ordered a Sandwich Cubano and it did not disappoint!
10/10 recommend
I love this place! Their empanas and pan de bono are on another level, 100 percent recommended!
Oh this is such a cute place! The staff is super friendly, they have amazing coffee choices, and small dishes to enjoy. I will be back!

Pedi un capuchino en leche de avena y me encantó!! El café definitivamente está en su punto, también ordené un sanduche cubano y fue perfecto.
El sitio es ideal para hacer takeo out y el servicio fue más que amable 🫶
Absolutely love this coffee shop! The coffee is consistently great every time I visit. A perfect spot for a quick pick-me-up! 🫶🏼
This place is awesome ! As soon as you get in you feel so welcome. The staff is very friendly and the coffee is delicious. I Highly recommend this place. I cant wait to come back.

This tiny coffee shop may have limited seating, but it’s big on aesthetics, efficiency, and quality. The stylish design and cozy vibes make it a charming stop. Baristas craft rich coffee, vibrant matcha, and refreshing smoothies with precision. Despite its size, this spot proves that great things come from small spaces.
The best coffee of my life, I love it!! The place is soooo nice and perfect for insta pics!
I loved the matcha here and the service was 5/5. I recommend coming here always. Jimena and Dani were amazing.
Obsessed with this cozy cafe in Southend. Everyone who works there is so sweet and has great customer service. The coffee and strawberry matcha are both so pretty and delicious!

This coffee shop is so cute and aesthetic to the eye! I love what they chose for the decor. The staff was so sweet and friendly from the moment you walk in. I really enjoyed their lattes and matcha, and their pan de bono is a must to try!
One of the best coffees I’ve ever tried! It will definitely be my regular spot for sure.
Me encanta el lugar muy acogedor y lindo. La atención 10/10 súper amables y serviciales. El strawberry Matcha es una delicia
Espectacular, me encantó el café y el lugar es demasiado hermoso. The best coffee in Charlotte! ☕️😍

Came across this coffee shop through Instagram, it really caught my eye from how aesthetic the place was, first impression when I came was the friendly and bubbly staff, the place was pretty busy but I got my drink fast, coming from a person who does not like matcha, I was convinced to give it a second try when I saw the beautiful drink, - I got the strawberry matcha, it was definitely one of the most delicious drinks I’ve tried! Only coming here for matcha now! Also their lattes are definitely worth a try!
amazing coffe shop the taste of the coffe is unique and the pastry delicious!!
The best matcha in Charlotte, they have the best syrups
Amazing place! The coffee is delicious, the food too. 10/10
I had the opportunity to visit this place in Charlotte. Best coffee I’ve ever had, so fresh…, they mix at the spot right in front of you, I also enjoyed their empanadas. Good job Babaloo!
The best coffee in Charlotte! Cozy place
Everything was delicious.
I ordered a matcha and they held the matcha and only gave me oatmilk lol

I will be honest.. I wanted to love this place, and it was straight up not good. I took the barista’s recommendation and got the ‘velvet amour’ espresso specialty drink and it tasted like straight almond milk. I did not even get a hint of espresso or flavoring. I threw it out and went to my favorite coffee place down the road which I have never done that before. I didn’t know you could mess up coffee that bad. Also soo expensive. $9 for a standard sized coffee is crazy especially when it wasn’t good. I am giving 2 stars because the place itself was very cute and quaint; however, as everyone else mentioned, there’s only two small tables to sit at so if you are looking for a place to go and catch up with a friend, this is not the place. Maybe I got the wrong drink, but I won’t be going back to try more. Waste of my time and money:(

After seeing countless videos & marketing for Babaloo, I begged my husband to deter from our usual coffee spots to try this place today.

The place was super cute & pretty. I’ve read reviews on the place being tiny and boy they were not wrong. It’s SO small! 2 tiny tables with a few chairs. Anyways, the coffee is pretty expensive. I got an iced vanilla latte & an iced fredo cappuccino and the total was $15. Apparently the fredo cappuccino is one of their most popular items but it was NOT good. The iced vanilla latte was pretty standard, but I couldn’t taste the vanilla at all.

I won’t be back, but south end did need more coffee shops, so I guess this does the job.

The South End drastically needed a coffee place ever since Central Coffee left a few years ago.  Serving La Colombe coffee beans gave me high hopes.  The mistake I made was going at three o’clock in the afternoon and expecting a hot cup of drip coffee.  $6+ later and I had a lukewarm cup of coffee which still tasted pretty good but would have been better if it were hot.  The service was quick and polite which was wonderful.

My friend got a latte and gave it an A+ review which was good to hear.

Don’t expect much of a “hang out and have a coffee” atmosphere because it is quite small inside.  That is fine because most people will get their coffee and then get on with their day.

Overall, this is a nice alternative to the unbelievably overpriced “café” at Wooden Robot and it supports a coffee business not named Starbucks.  I’d be willing to go back in the morning hours and get a, hopefully, hot cup of joe.

I think this is a cute on the go coffee shop. It’s more on the trendy aesthetic side and really small on the inside. I can see this place getting more busy during the summer when they can actually open up their garage door.

Overall, it was decent coffee. It’s tastes good and pleasant, but nothing that really stand outs. I think it has a lot of potential and can definitely get popular fast.

I wish the empanadas were a little bit packed more with meat/ filling, but overall prices were good. 6/10

My first time trying this cute little coffee shop and it’s absolutely delicious! I ordered the strawberry matcha and it had the perfect balance between all of the ingredients. Definitely going back for more! ☺️

I ordered 2 Strawberry Matcha w/ Oat Milk. Since it was a strawberry matcha, the strawberry purée over powered the taste of the matcha so it ended up tasting like Nesquik strawberry milk. Each of the drinks were almost $10 each which is quite pricey in my opinion for the size. I would’ve enjoyed it more if they added more matcha powdered or used a higher grade matcha. The cafe is very small and only had two tables for sitting. Definitely more of an order and go kinda place. It was kinda akward just standing in the middle to wait for my order since it was a little pack, not much room to move around. The ambiance of the cafe is cute though. Probably wouldn’t go out of my way to get but it was good to visit at-least once. I added a picture too of my matcha slightly mixed.

review_questions.Parking options: Paid parking lot, Paid street parking

reviews_data.review_text: This place is super cute and small. It has a couple of places inside to sit and a few tables outside. It's pretty busy. But I was excited to try it out. I ordered a cafe mocha or mocha latte (basically the same thing). I really wanted to like it, it was good, but it was not sweet in the slightest. It had a bland coffee taste to it. I don't like when my coffee is super sweet but a happy medium. This place is great, I wanted to love it, but make sure to ask for some sweetness if that's your thing. I can't speak on their other drinks or if they can make a better mocha, but for the price I spent (almost $8 for one 12 oz coffee), I wasn't very happy with it. I'm not sure I'll be back for this reason. I can't afford to try another drink and have it not work out. $8 was pretty steep.

review_questions.Parking options: Paid parking lot, Free street parking, Paid parking garage

reviews_data.review_text: Best cubano I have ever had. Their quatro leches was absolutely delicious. Dulce de leche latte was amazing too with the perfect balance of sweetness. Just happened to be in the area and did not expect to be blown away by their food, drinks, and service. Will be back for sure!

I loved the ambience! There are two tables here. Unfortunately I didn’t get the whole experience as these girls (customers) were sitting for 1.5+ hours, hogging the tables. Keep in mind to be considerate and mindful about others! Everyone else wants to also get the chance to sit there as well and enjoy the atmosphere. I think an ideal time would be 20 minutes max. The hot latte was delicious, I will definitely be back to try a few items they have on display.

Amazing and beautifully design - amazing customer service and delicious coffee and snacks!

music doesn’t quite match the energy of the space. I think a playlist with tropical house music or old latin style music would perfectly complement the vibe, bringing a vibrant, rhythmic touch that aligns beautifully with the setting. That said, everything else is absolutely top-notch.

The coffee is fresh and imported from Colombia! They were sold out of their popular strawberry matcha within the first hour of opening. Carolina and Emmanuel  (The owners) were amazing as always (if you’ve been to their other restaurants). The place is meant to be a stop and go cafe but it will not disappoint. There’s plenty of parking around the shop as well. Definitely will be stopping by whenever I’m around south end. Have coffee here in the morning and stop by El Puro or Muraya for dinner in the evening which are the other restaurants they own.
Coffee are fresh and hot. Pet friendly, service was so nice Caro and Dahianna took care of me really well. Definitely coming back!

reviews_data.review_text:
I tried the banana matcha, and it was pretty good—I'd give it around a 3.8 out of 5. I didn't try any food, but it looked tempting.

When I first walked up, I honestly felt like I was stepping into Spain—the atmosphere is stunning and very aesthetic. The indoor seating is cozy and a bit tight, so it’s not really a place to work comfortably, but there’s plenty of outdoor space to relax and enjoy.

The service was excellent—friendly and attentive.

Price-wise, I think it's a bit steep for a matcha, but all in all, it’s a cool spot. I plan to come back soon to try the food next time.

more of an aesthetic instagram coffee place than a good one. Tasted mediocre and the tiramisu latte just tasted like strong coffee. Expensive, wait is long, no where to sit and they messed up my order (they did fix it though). my bf loved the empanadas so I would come back for that, but driving out of the way for this coffee isn’t worth it.
They have the best matcha in CLT! We tried the blueberry banana matcha which was our favorite, and the popular strawberry matcha. The lady who made our matcha was super nice

Jimena was amazing! We went for coffee today and she had a line out the door and despite being all by herself she provided great customer service and always had a smile on her face. Coffee was delicious as always.
Place is DOPE🔥

After he ate too fast and got bad hiccups, he went to get some coffee to settle his stomach. While this place was really evolved and fun and had weird flavors, something that Mi Hijo likes, he got a double shot in his coffee!

And that’s when the trouble started, worse than when he’s had too much sugar. You better believe we took stock of the situation when he got home!

Very cool place, though!

review_questions.Noise level: Loud, but you can still talk

reviews_data.review_text: What a cool little spot to say the least! Good outdoor seating options, very cute and quaint cafe inside with a lot of menu options and a very creative drink menu. I felt like I asked a million questions to Alesandro and he patiently and diligently walked me through the whole menu (which he was extremely knowledgeable about) and ended up landing on the Biscoff Latte which had about 3 different layer and a very complex flavor profile and structure, but was very good! Would love to be me back as a treat!!
Love the industrial design. The coffee shop is not large, but cozy
Best matcha combination I’ve had. Love the pandan juice with matcha a lot.
My favorite coffee shop in the city!

I hate to be that person but..

I go to new coffee shop every two days to study and finish up some work. I always get the regular black coffee everywhere to try it.

The service and the young lady that was at the register were amazing, she was fast and very nice.

The coffee:- I did not even get to my third sip, I had to stop, the coffee tasted burnt and very over roasty taste.
I dont think I will be going back there for coffee but they have a nice patio outside and easy parking access on the street for a quick coffee.

They have interesting coffee and other drinks here. I love their strawberry matcha! The pastry case has just a few options, but they are all good. They have expanded their seating since they first opened and streamlined their service, so it’s faster.

i went here with my two friends and had a strawberry matcha which was the best strawberry matcha i’ve ever had, not very syurpy because they had actual purée! The matcha was smooth and very nice. My friend had the banana blueberry matcha and it was so creative and delicious i will probably get that next time, it was also a beautiful day so sitting in the spot with the big door open was really nice!  ( ^_^ )

Cute little coffee shop with outdoor sitting in addition to the quaint seating inside. The barista was friendly and my honey cinnamon oat milk latte is delicious.  My daughter enjoyed a Blue Cloud Banana Matcha.

The best coffee I have ever had! I stumbled upon this place and ordered the tiramisu latte and it was like a dessert - it was soooo good! The guy working there took his time making the drinks but you definitely get great quality coffee. Loved it!
Freddo cap & biscoff latte
Blue cloud banana matcha is the best matcha I have ever had! 10/10 quality and service! Will return!
Great 😊

I really wanted to love this place after seeing their matcha online—it looked amazing. The service was great and the barista was super friendly, which I appreciated. However, the matcha itself just didn’t live up to the hype. At $9, I was expecting something much better in terms of flavor and quality. The space is small, which I don’t mind at all, but unfortunately, the drink just didn’t deliver.

I went to this place for the first time on my break for an ice latte. Barista recommend a Freddy Cappuccino, that was out of this world, absolutely recommended. Service was great, if I have to choose a reason to come back will be the service.
Grwat coffee ane nice staff. The cuban sandwich is delicious
Small, cute & quaint shop with incredible service. One of the best Matchas in Charlotte hands down.
Waited inside 20 minutes for an online order. Staff didn’t even acknowledge me the entire time. Good coffee, but wont be back

Called in to order empanadas + pan de bono - to my surprise it was packed on a Sunday morning - yet my order was ready within minutes. Such a nice vibe and great customer service. Empanadas were delicious - pan de bono was a little thinner than other places I frequent but good taste - I’m glad to see the family grow in different businesses - good job Emanuel !!

review_questions.Parking options: Paid parking lot, Free street parking

reviews_data.review_text: Loved the strawberry matcha and their Cuban sandwich. Their pistachio milk is delicious. Been coming here since day one and babaloo just keep getting better. Their baristas are always so nice
Great coffee and staff! I love their strawberry matcha with pistachio milk. Their alt milks are delicious and they make it in house. Empanadas are also delicious

This coffee shop is absolutely beautiful, but the drinks were a huge letdown. With all the hype on Instagram, I had high expectations. I ordered the pistachio latte, hoping for a rich, flavorful drink, but it tasted like straight-up pistachio milk—no espresso at all. The service was great, but there’s no way this was worth $8. I don’t get how people actually enjoy these drinks.

cute place but the MILK is sooo gross. the drink itself was not good. i got a strawberry matcha and it was just so not good. any milk alternative is not good taste awful i had almond and oat and it was sooo nasty. wouldn’t recommend tbh cute place good service just the drinks itself not good.  could have such amazing potential if a few things were changed
Wonderful small shop with great people. Freddo cappuccino is a must try!

Ordered a strawberry matcha, it was not very enjoyable. Whatever oatmilk brand they use is not it. The strawberry did not come through well either. I came hoping to work from this spot but it is really only good for grab and go. Staff was nice though. I plan on never returning unfortunately.
Unimpressed watered down coffee late

Unfortunately I had high expectations for this place after seeing so many great reviews and IG posts I was eager to try. I love Colombian food so personally I wanted to try them out.

I ordered the strawberry matcha with oat milk and empanadas, unfortunately was disappointed. The matcha flavor was not present my drink tasted like low calorie strawberry nesquik. I’ve tried many other matcha’s from other coffee shops so definitely I was able to taste the difference.

The empanadas weren’t that bad but I’ve tried other places that have better options at a better price. The place is super small so it’s more like a quick to go option, hopefully they improve their matcha and buy better quality ingredients. But honestly, I wouldn’t recommend this place.

I recently visited Babaloo and was drawn in by the beautiful aesthetic; despite the location being very small with minimal space to wait in line/ wait for drinks.

As a matcha girly, I was really looking forward to trying their matcha, and unfortunately, it fell short of expectations. The flavor was overwhelmingly dominated by oat milk and strawberries, with barely any discernible matcha taste. It was a disappointment, especially given the high standards set by the shop's presence on social media, atmosphere and service.

I would not recommend. However, I do believe Babaloo has a lot of potential. The service was top-notch, with friendly and attentive staff who made me feel welcome.

Best thing about visiting this coffee place: seeing them give a fur baby a pup cup.

Probably the best Matcha I’ve had in the Charlotte area. Sweetest barista, and one of the only matchas I’ve had that I’ve loved without any cold foam. Top notch, and completely worth the slightly higher price point.
The best coffee I've tried in Charlotte, and such a great atmosphere! The craft drinks are made so perfectly, they're not overly sweet☕ Thanks so much, Babaloo coffee club, for the amazing service!
came here with a friend and we have both been around the world. it is really difficult to find quality coffee and matcha in the states, especially in charlotte. babaloo absolutely blew us away!
so fab,, so chic,, so cute!! to say its a vibe is an understatement. babaloos subtle wordly, koi taste is v refreshing 🍵🤍

Great Coffee, Amazing Food & Atmosphere

The coffee is solid, nothing extraordinary, but definitely good for the price. Where this place really shines is in its food and atmosphere. The design of the coffee shop is great, creating a welcoming and enjoyable vibe. I tried the chorizo and beef empanadas, and both were delicious, each served with its own sauce that complemented the flavors well. My only complaint is that the music was way too loud, but overall, it’s a fun spot worth visiting!

The aesthetic was very cute & trendy, but the cafe only has two really small tables for dine-in which is unfortunate if you want to sit & enjoy your items but I suppose works if you want to get your coffee to-go. The staff were very friendly! Overall, the food was reasonably priced, two items for $10. The mini empanada was good, the plain cappuccino was okay not great.

It's a cool little shop with good vibes and aesthetics, but the drinks were very disappointing for how expensive they are. The strawberry matcha barely had any strawberry or flavor, and the red velvet oatmilk latte tasted like oatmilk and nothing else. For the price your paying for the drinks, it's just not worth it for the lack of flavor. Good customer service and staff though.

Babaloo is a hidden gem for coffee lovers! The atmosphere is warm and inviting, perfect for catching up with friends.. I highly recommend their specialty drinks, especially the strawberry matcha 🍵🤍 The staff is friendly and attentive, making the experience even better. Plus, their pastries and snacks are delicious, with great options for different tastes like empanadas, or sandwiches. Plus some sweet like the cuatro leches cake or the alfajores (my favoriteeeeee). Babaloo is definitely worth a visit!

This coffee shop is really good! From the moment you walk in, the rich aroma of freshly brewed coffee fills the air. The flavors are bold, smooth, and perfectly balanced—just how real coffee should be!

The atmosphere is warm and inviting, with a cozy charm. It has a small indoor space; however, it’s a great place to connect with the community. I made great connections in less than an hour.
The staff is incredibly friendly and passionate about their craft, and they are also bilingual.

Babaloo is a must-visit. I highly recommend their matcha and their empanadas—absolutely tasty! Can't wait to come back.

Coffee was delicious, very unique way to serve it, what I love the most it’s that they don’t add too much of syrups so actually tastes like coffee, only thing that I didn’t like is the size of they sitting area hahahah I wish they added more space because the concept and the products are very nice.

Overall, it is a really cute little shop! It was so tiny inside that there wasn’t really anywhere to stand while you waited on your drink, which made it kind of awkward. One strawberry matcha was over $9, which feels a bit overpriced for the quality of the drink.
Best coffee shop in Charlotte! ⭐️. The turkey club sandwich was amazing!!. And is also pet friendly :)
Super excelente todo la atención de Daniela me hace volver por su buen servicio el café y el lugar super para una plática con las amigas

I absolutely loved Babaloo Coffee Club the first couple of times I went—it was so good that I even went back-to-back! I made two TikToks about it and referred a few friends because I was genuinely impressed.

However, my recent visits have been disappointing. I’ve been back three more times, and each time the strawberry matcha had less and less strawberry purée. Today, I even specifically asked them to please put the normal amount since the last time it was lacking, but I still only got one tiny layer. The strawberry matcha costs more than the regular matcha, so I expect a decent amount of strawberry, especially since their prices are higher than other matcha places I frequent.

I’m worried that they gave us their "best of the best" during their opening but are now slowly declining in quality. I do enjoy the empanadas, but at $4 each, they’re quite small and not filled enough to feel worth it.

I really hope they address these issues because I want to love this place as much as I did at first.
Love this place ! Everything is delicious, great and fast Service

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Drip Coffee, Carne Con Papas, NY Breakfast, Berries & Ganache
review_questions.Parking options: Free parking lot, Paid parking lot

reviews_data.review_text: Best matcha and pan de Bono’s 💌📩
The best Coffee Shop in Charlotte, the service is 10/10.
El café está genial y las empanadas súper. Fui con mi esposa y me encantó el fredo capuccino con dulce de leche

Sorry to leave a bad review. This place is tiny with two tables. Doesn’t have much of an ambience. The prices don’t make any sense. I buy a tall coffee at Starbucks for $2.87 and I thought that is expensive. These guys charge five dollars for a tall drip coffee. They also charge $.30 for cream. The breakfast sandwich was eight dollars and not that great. I spent 15 bucks for a coffee and a sandwich. The owner needs a reality check. Fix the quality of food and your prices and you may have a chance of surviving. My guess is they’re not gonna be open for too long.
Primera  y ultima vez que voy...mala atencion, todos apresurados y para el colmo mi cafe con un pelo

I ordered the strawberry matcha with an empanada. Best combo.
My husband ordered a Sandwich Cubano and it did not disappoint!
10/10 recommend
I love this place! Their empanas and pan de bono are on another level, 100 percent recommended!
Oh this is such a cute place! The staff is super friendly, they have amazing coffee choices, and small dishes to enjoy. I will be back!

Pedi un capuchino en leche de avena y me encantó!! El café definitivamente está en su punto, también ordené un sanduche cubano y fue perfecto.
El sitio es ideal para hacer takeo out y el servicio fue más que amable 🫶
Absolutely love this coffee shop! The coffee is consistently great every time I visit. A perfect spot for a quick pick-me-up! 🫶🏼
This place is awesome ! As soon as you get in you feel so welcome. The staff is very friendly and the coffee is delicious. I Highly recommend this place. I cant wait to come back.

This tiny coffee shop may have limited seating, but it’s big on aesthetics, efficiency, and quality. The stylish design and cozy vibes make it a charming stop. Baristas craft rich coffee, vibrant matcha, and refreshing smoothies with precision. Despite its size, this spot proves that great things come from small spaces.
The best coffee of my life, I love it!! The place is soooo nice and perfect for insta pics!
I loved the matcha here and the service was 5/5. I recommend coming here always. Jimena and Dani were amazing.
Obsessed with this cozy cafe in Southend. Everyone who works there is so sweet and has great customer service. The coffee and strawberry matcha are both so pretty and delicious!

This coffee shop is so cute and aesthetic to the eye! I love what they chose for the decor. The staff was so sweet and friendly from the moment you walk in. I really enjoyed their lattes and matcha, and their pan de bono is a must to try!
One of the best coffees I’ve ever tried! It will definitely be my regular spot for sure.
Me encanta el lugar muy acogedor y lindo. La atención 10/10 súper amables y serviciales. El strawberry Matcha es una delicia
Espectacular, me encantó el café y el lugar es demasiado hermoso. The best coffee in Charlotte! ☕️😍

Came across this coffee shop through Instagram, it really caught my eye from how aesthetic the place was, first impression when I came was the friendly and bubbly staff, the place was pretty busy but I got my drink fast, coming from a person who does not like matcha, I was convinced to give it a second try when I saw the beautiful drink, - I got the strawberry matcha, it was definitely one of the most delicious drinks I’ve tried! Only coming here for matcha now! Also their lattes are definitely worth a try!
amazing coffe shop the taste of the coffe is unique and the pastry delicious!!
The best matcha in Charlotte, they have the best syrups
Amazing place! The coffee is delicious, the food too. 10/10
I had the opportunity to visit this place in Charlotte. Best coffee I’ve ever had, so fresh…, they mix at the spot right in front of you, I also enjoyed their empanadas. Good job Babaloo!
The best coffee in Charlotte! Cozy place
Everything was delicious.
I ordered a matcha and they held the matcha and only gave me oatmilk lol

I will be honest.. I wanted to love this place, and it was straight up not good. I took the barista’s recommendation and got the ‘velvet amour’ espresso specialty drink and it tasted like straight almond milk. I did not even get a hint of espresso or flavoring. I threw it out and went to my favorite coffee place down the road which I have never done that before. I didn’t know you could mess up coffee that bad. Also soo expensive. $9 for a standard sized coffee is crazy especially when it wasn’t good. I am giving 2 stars because the place itself was very cute and quaint; however, as everyone else mentioned, there’s only two small tables to sit at so if you are looking for a place to go and catch up with a friend, this is not the place. Maybe I got the wrong drink, but I won’t be going back to try more. Waste of my time and money:(

After seeing countless videos & marketing for Babaloo, I begged my husband to deter from our usual coffee spots to try this place today.

The place was super cute & pretty. I’ve read reviews on the place being tiny and boy they were not wrong. It’s SO small! 2 tiny tables with a few chairs. Anyways, the coffee is pretty expensive. I got an iced vanilla latte & an iced fredo cappuccino and the total was $15. Apparently the fredo cappuccino is one of their most popular items but it was NOT good. The iced vanilla latte was pretty standard, but I couldn’t taste the vanilla at all.

I won’t be back, but south end did need more coffee shops, so I guess this does the job.

The South End drastically needed a coffee place ever since Central Coffee left a few years ago.  Serving La Colombe coffee beans gave me high hopes.  The mistake I made was going at three o’clock in the afternoon and expecting a hot cup of drip coffee.  $6+ later and I had a lukewarm cup of coffee which still tasted pretty good but would have been better if it were hot.  The service was quick and polite which was wonderful.

My friend got a latte and gave it an A+ review which was good to hear.

Don’t expect much of a “hang out and have a coffee” atmosphere because it is quite small inside.  That is fine because most people will get their coffee and then get on with their day.

Overall, this is a nice alternative to the unbelievably overpriced “café” at Wooden Robot and it supports a coffee business not named Starbucks.  I’d be willing to go back in the morning hours and get a, hopefully, hot cup of joe.

I think this is a cute on the go coffee shop. It’s more on the trendy aesthetic side and really small on the inside. I can see this place getting more busy during the summer when they can actually open up their garage door.

Overall, it was decent coffee. It’s tastes good and pleasant, but nothing that really stand outs. I think it has a lot of potential and can definitely get popular fast.

I wish the empanadas were a little bit packed more with meat/ filling, but overall prices were good. 6/10

My first time trying this cute little coffee shop and it’s absolutely delicious! I ordered the strawberry matcha and it had the perfect balance between all of the ingredients. Definitely going back for more! ☺️

I ordered 2 Strawberry Matcha w/ Oat Milk. Since it was a strawberry matcha, the strawberry purée over powered the taste of the matcha so it ended up tasting like Nesquik strawberry milk. Each of the drinks were almost $10 each which is quite pricey in my opinion for the size. I would’ve enjoyed it more if they added more matcha powdered or used a higher grade matcha. The cafe is very small and only had two tables for sitting. Definitely more of an order and go kinda place. It was kinda akward just standing in the middle to wait for my order since it was a little pack, not much room to move around. The ambiance of the cafe is cute though. Probably wouldn’t go out of my way to get but it was good to visit at-least once. I added a picture too of my matcha slightly mixed.

review_questions.Parking options: Paid parking lot, Paid street parking

reviews_data.review_text: This place is super cute and small. It has a couple of places inside to sit and a few tables outside. It's pretty busy. But I was excited to try it out. I ordered a cafe mocha or mocha latte (basically the same thing). I really wanted to like it, it was good, but it was not sweet in the slightest. It had a bland coffee taste to it. I don't like when my coffee is super sweet but a happy medium. This place is great, I wanted to love it, but make sure to ask for some sweetness if that's your thing. I can't speak on their other drinks or if they can make a better mocha, but for the price I spent (almost $8 for one 12 oz coffee), I wasn't very happy with it. I'm not sure I'll be back for this reason. I can't afford to try another drink and have it not work out. $8 was pretty steep.

review_questions.Parking options: Paid parking lot, Free street parking, Paid parking garage

reviews_data.review_text: Best cubano I have ever had. Their quatro leches was absolutely delicious. Dulce de leche latte was amazing too with the perfect balance of sweetness. Just happened to be in the area and did not expect to be blown away by their food, drinks, and service. Will be back for sure!

I loved the ambience! There are two tables here. Unfortunately I didn’t get the whole experience as these girls (customers) were sitting for 1.5+ hours, hogging the tables. Keep in mind to be considerate and mindful about others! Everyone else wants to also get the chance to sit there as well and enjoy the atmosphere. I think an ideal time would be 20 minutes max. The hot latte was delicious, I will definitely be back to try a few items they have on display.

Amazing and beautifully design - amazing customer service and delicious coffee and snacks!

music doesn’t quite match the energy of the space. I think a playlist with tropical house music or old latin style music would perfectly complement the vibe, bringing a vibrant, rhythmic touch that aligns beautifully with the setting. That said, everything else is absolutely top-notch.

The coffee is fresh and imported from Colombia! They were sold out of their popular strawberry matcha within the first hour of opening. Carolina and Emmanuel  (The owners) were amazing as always (if you’ve been to their other restaurants). The place is meant to be a stop and go cafe but it will not disappoint. There’s plenty of parking around the shop as well. Definitely will be stopping by whenever I’m around south end. Have coffee here in the morning and stop by El Puro or Muraya for dinner in the evening which are the other restaurants they own.
Coffee are fresh and hot. Pet friendly, service was so nice Caro and Dahianna took care of me really well. Definitely coming back!

raw_data.description: In the eclectic South End neighborhood, Babaloo Coffee Club invites you to indulge in a world of exquisite flavors. Step inside and be greeted by the rich aroma of freshly brewed coffee, enticing sandwiches, handcrafted empanadas, and delectable seasonal sweets. Unwind in a warm and inviting ambiance, perfect for catching up with friends. Babaloo Coffee Club is your go-to destination for a delightful sensory journey that celebrates the art of coffee
